snippet.textDisplay:
Once again I'm sorry but.......THIS is not true contemporary as what you would see in stage. It's overly emotive, gymnastic tricks and aerial with mixtures of ballet. This is what we British would call Lyrical!!!! It's awesome in its own context but please stop calling It contemporary. I am tired of it. Contemporary isn't always (very rarely!!!) Performed to pop chart music.

I want to see choreograhic risks, more intelligent choreography.

The dancers themselves fair play are wonderful to watch, excellent technique. Well done, happy for you but I cant support this as a contemporary dance artist myself.
